projectTypes.name: Assembly
projectTypes.description: Buildings where people gather for various purposes such as entertainment, worship, recreation, or similar activities. Examples include theaters, concert halls, arenas, and stadiums.

projectTypes.name: Business/Commercial
projectTypes.description: Buildings used for office, professional, or service-type transactions. This includes facilities like banks, offices and service-oriented businesses.

projectTypes.name: Educational
projectTypes.description: Buildings used for educational purposes, such as schools, daycares, and facilities where children or adults receive instruction or training.

projectTypes.name: Factory/Industrial
projectTypes.description: Buildings designed for manufacturing, assembling, and industrial processes. These structures are used for the production of goods and materials, such as factories, warehouses, and processing plants.

projectTypes.name: Hazardous
projectTypes.description: Buildings used for the storage, processing, or handling of hazardous materials such as chemicals, explosives, or flammable substances. This category includes facilities that deal with toxic, corrosive, or dangerous materials.

projectTypes.name: Institutional
projectTypes.description: Buildings used for the care and supervision of people who are typically incapable of self-preservation due to medical, psychological, or similar reasons. Examples include hospitals, nursing homes, prisons, and daycare centers.

projectTypes.name: Mercantile
projectTypes.description: Buildings used for the display and sale of merchandise. This includes retail stores, shopping malls, and showrooms where goods are sold directly to consumers.

projectTypes.name: Residential
projectTypes.description: Buildings intended for people to live in. This includes both single-family homes and multi-family buildings like apartments, condominiums, and townhouses.

projectTypes.name: Storage
projectTypes.description: Buildings primarily used for the storage of goods, materials, or products. This includes warehouses, self-storage units, and storage facilities.

projectTypes.name: Utility and Miscellaneous
projectTypes.description: Buildings and structures that do not fit into the other categories. This includes agricultural buildings, utility structures, barns, sheds, and towers.

specialRequirements.requirement: Fire safety systems must be up to code

seismicSafety.requirements: No seismic-specific design requirements due to low seismic risk in the state

energyEfficiency.solarMandate: No statewide solar panel mandate, though incentives available for solar installations
energyEfficiency.efficiencyStandards: High energy efficiency standards for lighting, insulation, HVAC systems

wildfireSafety.requirements: No specific statewide wildfire safety requirements due to low risk, but local governments may have their own regulations

floodSafety.requirements: Elevation requirements for buildings in flood zones, flood-proofing, and flood-resistant materials

hurricaneSafety.requirements: Hurricane-resistant construction, impact-resistant windows, wind load standards, and roofing materials designed for high winds

fireSafety.fireEscapeRequirements: Standardized fire exits, smoke detectors, fire alarms, and sprinkler systems
